title: Coffeehouse sounds are big hits for Duncan Sheik, Suzanne Vega
text:
Photo: Shervin Lainez Duncan Sheik had the most played song of 1997 with “Barely Breathing,” from his self-titled debut album. Duncan Sheik had the most played song of 1997 with “Barely...
Hosting a variety of traditional music styles ranging from bluegrass, folk and classical to Americana, jazz and international, the Freight & Salvage Coffeehouse in Berkeley is presenting three singer-songwriters next month who have commercial radio singles in their back catalogs.
